The paper deals with online learning of finite Markov decision process (MDP) problems, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of side information also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The proposed algorithm and its regret analysis are computational in nature, indicating a possible fit with computer engineering (cs.CE). Overall, the most likely sub-categories are those related to machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS).
